1  
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:06,000  
Vietnam is Calling. Are You Ready to Answer?

2  
00:00:06,001 --> 00:00:14,000  
If you’ve been scrolling through your feed lately, chances are you’ve seen more and more travelers posting dreamy footage of Vietnam.

3  
00:00:14,001 --> 00:00:20,000  
From glowing lanterns in Hoi An to steaming bowls of phở on busy sidewalks,  

4  
00:00:20,001 --> 00:00:25,000  
From mountain views in Sa Pa to the turquoise waves of Phu Quoc —  

5  
00:00:25,001 --> 00:00:31,000  
Vietnam is quietly (or maybe not so quietly) becoming one of the world’s most talked-about destinations.

6  
00:00:31,001 --> 00:00:36,000  
This growing trend, known simply as "Vietnam is calling," is more than just a hashtag —  

7  
00:00:36,001 --> 00:00:41,000  
It’s a heartfelt invitation to experience something unforgettable.

8  
00:00:41,001 --> 00:00:46,000  
Vietnam is a country that doesn’t just ask to be seen — it begs to be felt, tasted, and remembered.

9  
00:00:46,001 --> 00:00:52,000  
The natural beauty here is nothing short of breathtaking.

10  
00:00:52,001 --> 00:01:00,000  
In the north, towering rice terraces curve along misty mountainsides, while limestone cliffs rise from the waters of Hạ Long Bay like scenes from a fantasy film.

11  
00:01:00,001 --> 00:01:08,000  
In the center and south, you’ll find wide golden beaches, ancient caves, and lush national parks.

12  
00:01:08,001 --> 00:01:13,000  
Where you can trek, swim, or simply breathe in the fresh air and the silence of nature.

13  
00:01:13,001 --> 00:01:18,000  
Vietnam offers landscapes that shift with every region, and every turn feels like a new postcard.

14  
00:01:18,001 --> 00:01:25,000  
But Vietnam’s magic doesn’t end with scenery. In fact, for many visitors, the true highlight is the food.

15  
00:01:25,001 --> 00:01:31,000  
Vietnamese cuisine is bold, fresh, and deeply satisfying — and perhaps best of all, it’s everywhere.

16  
00:01:31,001 --> 00:01:36,000  
You don’t need to find a five-star restaurant to enjoy a five-star meal.

17  
00:01:36,001 --> 00:01:43,000  
On nearly every corner, a street vendor is grilling, frying, wrapping, or pouring something delicious.

18  
00:01:43,001 --> 00:01:49,000  
Phở, bánh mì, bún chả, bánh xèo, cà phê sữa đá — each dish is a flavor story.

19  
00:01:49,001 --> 00:01:53,000  
Trying them all becomes a joyful daily ritual.

20  
00:01:53,001 --> 00:01:57,000  
It’s no wonder foodies from around the world are now calling Vietnam a street food paradise.

21  
00:01:57,001 --> 00:02:02,000  
Beyond the plates and the landscapes, Vietnam also offers something rich and rare:  

22  
00:02:02,001 --> 00:02:06,000  
A culture that is both ancient and alive.

23  
00:02:06,001 --> 00:02:10,000  
You can feel it in the centuries-old temples, the royal architecture of Hue,  

24  
00:02:10,001 --> 00:02:14,000  
The poetic old town of Hoi An, and the vibrant street life of Ha Noi and Sai Gon.

25  
00:02:14,001 --> 00:02:19,000  
Vietnam’s history is deep, its traditions well-preserved, and its people proudly connected to their heritage.

26  
00:02:19,001 --> 00:02:24,000  
At the same time, the country pulses with energy and creativity, especially among its youth.

27  
00:02:24,001 --> 00:02:28,000  
There’s a rhythm to life here — a balance between old and new — that keeps things endlessly fascinating.

28  
00:02:28,001 --> 00:02:34,000  
Whether you’re an adventurer, a beach lover, a digital nomad, or a soul-searcher, Vietnam meets you where you are.

29  
00:02:34,001 --> 00:02:39,000  
You can ride a scooter through the countryside, sip cocktails on a rooftop in Da Nang,  

30  
00:02:39,001 --> 00:02:44,000  
Learn to cook with locals, or spend the night in a bamboo hut by a river.

31  
00:02:44,001 --> 00:02:47,000  
The options are endless, and they all come with a sense of discovery.

32  
00:02:47,001 --> 00:02:52,000  
And then there are the people. What truly makes Vietnam unforgettable is its warmth.

33  
00:02:52,001 --> 00:02:57,000  
Not just in the climate, but in its hearts. The Vietnamese are famously friendly, generous, and proud of their home.

34  
00:02:57,001 --> 00:03:02,000  
Travelers often leave with stories of strangers who became guides, helpers, or even friends.

35  
00:03:02,001 --> 00:03:06,000  
You’ll be greeted with smiles, kindness, and a genuine curiosity.

36  
00:03:06,001 --> 00:03:10,000  
That makes you feel not just welcome, but wanted.

37  
00:03:10,001 --> 00:03:16,000  
So yes, Vietnam is calling. And it’s calling now more than ever — through every photo, every glowing review,

38  
00:03:16,001 --> 00:03:20,000  
And every traveler who came, saw, and fell in love.

39  
00:03:20,001 --> 00:03:24,000  
This is a country that doesn’t just offer a vacation — it offers a connection.

40  
00:03:24,001 --> 00:03:28,000  
If you're looking for your next journey, one that touches your senses and your soul,  

41  
00:03:28,001 --> 00:03:32,000  
Then maybe it's time to stop scrolling and start packing.

42  
00:03:32,001 --> 00:03:36,000  
Vietnam is calling. Will you answer?